Durban - A man was killed on the N2 highway in Durban after a collision between two trucks after the M7 on Monday afternoon. Rescue Care paramedics responded to the scene of the incident and found that the two trucks had collided in a rear end collision. “The passenger of the rear truck was found to be severely entrapped in the wreckage. He had sustained major injuries and was declared deceased on the scene by Paramedics,” said Garrith Jamieson, Rescue Care Operations Director. Jamieson said the driver had sustained moderate injuries and was stabilised on scene by Advanced Life Support Paramedics before being transported to a nearby hospital. He said the occupants of the second vehicle were not injured. He also said the the events leading up to the collision is unknown but police were on scene and are investigating. In another incident, a biker was left seriously injured after crashing with another vehicle in Pinetown on Monday morning. “Rescue Care Paramedics arrived on the scene just after 8am to find the biker in the sidewalk having sustained serious injuries. Advanced Life Support Paramedics worked to stabilise the man on the scene before transporting him to a nearby hospital for the further care that he required,” he said. In the afternoon, a mother and her child were left injured after the car they were travelling in crashed into a truck on the M7. “Just after 3pm Rescue Care Paramedics arrived on the scene to find the mother and child still inside their vehicle. They had sustained moderate injuries and Advanced Life Support Paramedics stabilised them in the vehicle before carefully extricating them and placing them into an awaiting ambulance,” he said. Events leading to the crashes are unknown but police were on scene and are investigating. Daily News